   <mods:abstract>If nice weather, Samuel, William and Bill shall set out tomorrow. Sent
            tobacco by Samuel. As for PeterÆs upcoming journey, he should bring apples and whatever
            else his physicians think would be conducive to his health and comfort. Is Mrs. Judith
            WatkinÆs receipt for the money from General Clarkson in the black trunk? Is sending down
            two bank books; give Samuel 100 pounds from that so John Jay can pay his workmen. Winter
            is approaching; but should not forget about the quality of accommodations etc. for
            PeterÆs visit in the haste of leaving. Hopes he returns from his trip in perfect
            health.</mods:abstract>
